      "writtenOn": "2026-04-20T19:49:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for updating the docs.\n\n\u003e Don\u0027t want to introduce regressions, since sorting was previously done preserving it in new constructor too.\n\nI\u0027m still not 100% sold on that. It\u0027s a new constructor that intentionally has different behavior for traits. Why keep `SORTED` special? If you want a helper so that callers don\u0027t have to do the sorting themselves, you could add that as a static method `createFromUnsorted(Collection\u003cRef\u003e refs, EnumSet\u003cPackedRefsTrait\u003e traits)`, but calling that instead of doing `new RefWriter(RefComparator.sort(myRefs), EnumSet.of(PackedRefsTrait.SORTED))` seems a little silly. I think we\u0027re more likely to sort twice by accident if we always try to sort in the constructor (and that\u0027s at least O(n) runtime cost + extra memory used for the list copy).",
      "parentUuid": "4f9339ba_f891a283",
      "revId": "d32f41eb16c67ed51b2a9e72107e607263ea2e7e",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
