      "writtenOn": "2026-04-20T22:36:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, interesting point about the RefWriter being abstract. Although the name does not imply it, the comments for the class do imply that this is a packed-refs file format. That implication tells us that this trait behavior is appropriate for all subclasses? i.e. subclasses just write to the network potentially instead of a file, but subclasses will not be reftables implementations?",
      "parentUuid": "5509d9d6_9e9ed38a",
      "revId": "d32f41eb16c67ed51b2a9e72107e607263ea2e7e",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
